# Deferred Tier 3 — Implementation Plan

3 remaining features. **#24 Collaboration** requires invite/auth infrastructure and is deferred further.

## Proposed Changes

### #20 — Collections / Folders

Group mocks into named projects for better organization.

#### Backend

##### [NEW] [Collection.js](file:///d:/MockFlow/server/models/Collection.js)

Mongoose model:
- `name` (String, required)
- `description` (String, optional)
- `color` (String, hex or preset name)
- `userId` (String, indexed)
- `createdAt` (Date)

##### [MODIFY] [Mock.js](file:///d:/MockFlow/server/models/Mock.js)

Add optional `collectionId` field referencing a Collection.

##### [MODIFY] [index.js](file:///d:/MockFlow/server/index.js)

New endpoints:
- `POST /collections` — create collection
- `GET /collections` — list user's collections
- `PUT /collections/:id` — rename/recolor
- `DELETE /collections/:id` — delete (unlinks mocks, doesn't delete them)
- `PUT /mocks/:id` — already exists, add `collectionId` field support

#### Frontend

##### [NEW] [CollectionManager.tsx](file:///d:/MockFlow/client/src/components/CollectionManager.tsx)

Rendered above the mock list on Your Mocks page:
- Horizontal scroll row of collection pills (colored dots + name)
- "All" pill (default, shows all mocks)
- "+ New" pill to create collection via inline input
- Clicking a pill filters mocks by that collection
- Right-click or "..." menu on pill → rename, change color, delete

##### [MODIFY] [MockList.tsx](file:///d:/MockFlow/client/src/components/MockList.tsx)

- Accept `activeCollection` filter prop
- Filter mocks by `collectionId` when a collection is selected
- Add collection assignment dropdown per mock card (colored dot + name)
- PATCH mock's `collectionId` on selection

##### [MODIFY] [App.tsx](file:///d:/MockFlow/client/src/App.tsx)

- Render `<CollectionManager>` on Mocks page, manage `activeCollection` state

---

### #22 — Response Schema Builder (Simplified)

Visual field builder for JSON responses — simplified version (not drag-and-drop).

##### [NEW] [SchemaBuilder.tsx](file:///d:/MockFlow/client/src/components/SchemaBuilder.tsx)

A tabbed alternative to the raw JSON editor on the Create Mock page:
- Two tabs: **Raw JSON** (existing editor) | **Schema Builder** (new)
- Schema Builder shows a list of fields with: name input, type dropdown (string/number/boolean/array/object), value input
- "Add Field" button to add new rows
- Auto-generates JSON from the field list and syncs to the response state
- No backend needed — purely frontend

##### [MODIFY] [MockForm.tsx](file:///d:/MockFlow/client/src/components/MockForm.tsx)

- Add tab toggle between Raw JSON and Schema Builder
- Both tabs share the same `response` state

---

## Deferred

| # | Feature | Reason |
|---|---------|--------|
| 24 | Collaboration | Needs invite system, shared access control, email notifications |

## Verification Plan

### Browser Testing
- **Collections**: Create a collection, assign mocks to it, filter by collection, rename, delete
- **Schema Builder**: Switch between Raw JSON / Schema Builder tabs, add fields, verify generated JSON
